### Q7. What is the N+1 query problem?
The N+1 query problem occurs when an application executes 1 initial query to fetch a list of N parent records, and then executes N subsequent queries to fetch the associated child data for each individual parent.

> **Example:** You fetch 100 `MenuItem` records (1 query). If you then loop through them and call `.getCategory().getName()` on an un-fetched lazy relationship, Hibernate will fire 100 individual queries to look up each category. Total queries = 1 + 100 = 101.

