### Q13. Why write private mapper methods (entity <-> dto)?
* **Decoupling:** Prevents internal database schemas (Entities) from leaking to the outside world/API client (DTOs).
* **Security:** Avoids exposing internal IDs, password hashes, or audit fields (`createdAt`, `updatedAt`) that clients don't need to see or modify.
* **Cleanliness:** Keeps mapping logic isolated, highly testable, and out of your core business logic methods.